<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 2000, 4000 &#38; 8000 MODELS - TROUBLESHOOTING
        - TESTING FOR POWER TO THE CONTROLLER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING FOR POWER TO THE CONTROLLER</title>
        <para>This test should be performed after
            <hotlnk document="s04033_9.xml" xrefid="t0403303">INSPECTION FOR ILLUMINATED LEDS, PART A</hotlnk>, and one
            of the following conditions is present with the key ON: 1. The Green VLT is not illuminated and no Red LEDs
            are illuminated. 2. The Green VLT LED is flashing.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Batteries must be fully charged for this test.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t0403305" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing For Power to the Controller</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.64in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.65in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.49in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.94in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.33in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="1to7"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>TEST POINTS</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check 30A fuse (298).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Fuse (298).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect 30-way connector (288) from the controller. Key ON-Measure voltage to
                                chassis ground at harness connector terminals B1, K2, K3.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(288) B1, K2, K3 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 4.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure voltage between terminal B1 and terminals A1, A2, A3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>B1 to A1, A2, A3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Controller power and ground circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in ground circuit between connector (288) and frame ground where terminal
                                voltage (A1, A2, A3) was less than 10 volts, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove ABS power relay from connector (R3). Measure voltage to ground at circuit
                                94A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(R3) circuit 94A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 94A from 30A fuse (298), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (R3) measure voltage between circuits 94A and 94GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(R3) 94A to 94GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in gnd. circuit 94GC between conn. (R3) and ground, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (R3) measure voltage between circuits 94F and 94GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(R3) 94F to 94GC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 13K from fuse (299), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (R3) use a test lead to jumper circuit 94A to 94K. At connector (288),
                                measure voltage to ground at terminals B1, K2, K3.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(R3) 94A to 94K, (288) B1, K2, K3 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the power relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in circuits between connectors (R3) and (288), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
